title: Enceladus Up Close, with Carolyn Porco - StarTalk All-Stars
description: Is the subsurface ocean on Saturn’s moon Enceladus the most likely place in our solar system to harbor life? Dive in with StarTalk All-Stars host and planetary scientist Carolyn Porco, guest NASA astrobiologist Chris McKay, and co-host Chuck Nice.
author: feed@startalkradio.net (Neil deGrasse Tyson)
